<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900810-0028</DOCNO><DOCID>900810-0028.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Sierra Pacific Resources:   Nevada Utility Cancels Plan   For Thousand Springs Plant</HL><DATE>08/10/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14</SO><CO>   SRP BPCO FWC WX</CO><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)</IN><LP>   Sierra Pacific Resources said market uncertainty hascaused it to cancel the development of the Thousand Springselectric generation project resulting in a $35 million chargeon the utility's 1990 earnings. The Reno, Nev., utilityholding company posted earnings of $44.9 million, or $2.05 ashare, in 1989.   Although several purchase proposals were submitted bypotential energy buyers, the company said it was unable toobtain long-term purchase agreements necessary to sustain theproject, planned for construction in Elko, Nev.</LP><TEXT>   Sierra Pacific was the project manager and largestparticipant in this independent power project. In the pastfew weeks, four companies, Bonneville Pacific Corp.; FosterWheeler Energy Corp.; The Pittsburgh andamp; Midway Coal MiningCo.; and Westinghouse Electric Corp. have withdrawn from theproject, company officials said.</TEXT></DOC>